To combine the terms \(-\tfrac{3}{8}-\tfrac{x}{11}\), use the common denominator \(88\):

\[
-\frac{3}{8}-\frac{x}{11}
=-\frac{3\cdot11}{88}-\frac{x\cdot8}{88}
=\frac{-33-8x}{88}
=\frac{-(8x+33)}{88}.
\]

